154static std::optional<Seconds>& transientActivationDurationOverrideForTesting()
155{
156 static NeverDestroyed<std::optional<Seconds>> overrideForTesting;
157 return overrideForTesting;
158}
159
160static Seconds transientActivationDuration()
161{
162 if (auto override = transientActivationDurationOverrideForTesting())
163 return *override;
164 return defaultTransientActivationDuration;

183static void addUnloadEventListener(DOMWindow* domWindow)
184{
185 if (windowsWithUnloadEventListeners().add(domWindow).isNewEntry)
186 domWindow->disableSuddenTermination();
187}

189static void removeUnloadEventListener(DOMWindow* domWindow)

191 if (windowsWithUnloadEventListeners().remove(domWindow))
192 domWindow->enableSuddenTermination();
193}

219static bool allowsBeforeUnloadListeners(DOMWindow* window)
220{
221 ASSERT_ARG(window, window);
222 Frame* frame = window->frame();
223 if (!frame)
224 return false;
225 if (!frame->page())
226 return false;
227 return frame->isMainFrame();
228}
229
230bool DOMWindow::dispatchAllPendingBeforeUnloadEvents()
231{
232 DOMWindowSet& set = windowsWithBeforeUnloadEventListeners();
233 if (set.isEmpty())
234 return true;
235
236 static bool alreadyDispatched = false;
237 ASSERT(!alreadyDispatched);
238 if (alreadyDispatched)
239 return true;
240
241 Vector<Ref<DOMWindow>> windows;
242 windows.reserveInitialCapacity(set.size());
243 for (auto& window : set)
244 windows.uncheckedAppend(*window.key);
245
246 for (auto& window : windows) {
247 if (!set.contains(window.ptr()))
248 continue;
249
250 Frame* frame = window->frame();
251 if (!frame)
252 continue;
253
254 if (!frame->loader().shouldClose())
255 return false;
256
257 window->enableSuddenTermination();
258 }
259
260 alreadyDispatched = true;
261 return true;
262}
263
264unsigned DOMWindow::pendingUnloadEventListeners() const
265{
266 return windowsWithUnloadEventListeners().count(const_cast<DOMWindow*>(this));
267}
268
269void DOMWindow::dispatchAllPendingUnloadEvents()
270{
271 DOMWindowSet& set = windowsWithUnloadEventListeners();
272 if (set.isEmpty())
273 return;
274
275 static bool alreadyDispatched = false;
276 ASSERT(!alreadyDispatched);
277 if (alreadyDispatched)
278 return;
279
280 auto windows = WTF::map(set, [] (auto& keyValue) {
281 return Ref<DOMWindow>(*(keyValue.key));
282 });
283
284 for (auto& window : windows) {
285 if (!set.contains(window.ptr()))
286 continue;
287
288 window->dispatchEvent(PageTransitionEvent::create(eventNames().pagehideEvent, false), window->document());
289 window->dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().unloadEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No), window->document());
290
291 window->enableSuddenTermination();
292 }
293
294 alreadyDispatched = true;
295}

297// This function:
298// 1) Validates the pending changes are not changing any value to NaN; in that case keep original value.
299// 2) Constrains the window rect to the minimum window size and no bigger than the float rect's dimensions.
300// 3) Constrains the window rect to within the top and left boundaries of the available screen rect.
301// 4) Constrains the window rect to within the bottom and right boundaries of the available screen rect.
302// 5) Translate the window rect coordinates to be within the coordinate space of the screen.
303FloatRect DOMWindow::adjustWindowRect(Page& page, const FloatRect& pendingChanges)
304{
305 FloatRect screen = screenAvailableRect(page.mainFrame().view());
306 FloatRect window = page.chrome().windowRect();
307
308 // Make sure we're in a valid state before adjusting dimensions.
309 ASSERT(std::isfinite(screen.x()));
310 ASSERT(std::isfinite(screen.y()));
311 ASSERT(std::isfinite(screen.width()));
312 ASSERT(std::isfinite(screen.height()));
313 ASSERT(std::isfinite(window.x()));
314 ASSERT(std::isfinite(window.y()));
315 ASSERT(std::isfinite(window.width()));
316 ASSERT(std::isfinite(window.height()));
317
318 // Update window values if new requested values are not NaN.
319 if (!std::isnan(pendingChanges.x()))
320 window.setX(pendingChanges.x());
321 if (!std::isnan(pendingChanges.y()))
322 window.setY(pendingChanges.y());
323 if (!std::isnan(pendingChanges.width()))
324 window.setWidth(pendingChanges.width());
325 if (!std::isnan(pendingChanges.height()))
326 window.setHeight(pendingChanges.height());
327
328 FloatSize minimumSize = page.chrome().client().minimumWindowSize();
329 window.setWidth(std::min(std::max(minimumSize.width(), window.width()), screen.width()));
330 window.setHeight(std::min(std::max(minimumSize.height(), window.height()), screen.height()));
331
332 // Constrain the window position within the valid screen area.
333 window.setX(std::max(screen.x(), std::min(window.x(), screen.maxX() - window.width())));
334 window.setY(std::max(screen.y(), std::min(window.y(), screen.maxY() - window.height())));
335
336 return window;
337}

339bool DOMWindow::allowPopUp(Frame& firstFrame)
340{
341 if (DocumentLoader* documentLoader = firstFrame.loader().documentLoader()) {
342 // If pop-up policy was set during navigation, use it. If not, use the global settings.
343 PopUpPolicy popUpPolicy = documentLoader->popUpPolicy();
344 if (popUpPolicy == PopUpPolicy::Allow)
345 return true;
346
347 if (popUpPolicy == PopUpPolicy::Block)
348 return false;
349 }
350
351 return UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGesture()
352 || firstFrame.settings().javaScriptCanOpenWindowsAutomatically();
353}
354
355bool DOMWindow::allowPopUp()
356{
357 auto* frame = this->frame();
358 return frame && allowPopUp(*frame);
359}

361bool DOMWindow::canShowModalDialog(const Frame& frame)
362{
363 // Override support for layout testing purposes.
364 if (auto* document = frame.document()) {
365 if (auto* window = document->domWindow()) {
366 if (window->m_canShowModalDialogOverride)
367 return window->m_canShowModalDialogOverride.value();
368 }
369 }
370
371 auto* page = frame.page();
372 return page && page->chrome().canRunModal();
373}

393void DOMWindow::didSecureTransitionTo(Document& document)
394{
395 observeContext(&document);
396
397 // The Window is being transferred from one document to another so we need to reset data
398 // members that store the window's document (rather than the window itself).
399 m_crypto = nullptr;
400 m_navigator = nullptr;
401 m_performance = nullptr;
402}

404void DOMWindow::prewarmLocalStorageIfNecessary()
405{
406 auto* page = this->page();
407
408 // No need to prewarm for ephemeral sessions since the data is in memory only.
409 if (!page || page->usesEphemeralSession())
410 return;
411
412 if (!page->mainFrame().mayPrewarmLocalStorage())
413 return;
414
415 // This eagerly constructs the StorageArea, which will load items from disk.
416 auto localStorageResult = this->localStorage();
417 if (localStorageResult.hasException())
418 return;
419
420 auto* localStorage = localStorageResult.returnValue();
421 if (!localStorage)
422 return;
423
424 page->mainFrame().didPrewarmLocalStorage();
425}

427DOMWindow::~DOMWindow()
428{
429 if (m_suspendedForDocumentSuspension)
430 willDestroyCachedFrame();
431 else
432 willDestroyDocumentInFrame();
433
434 removeAllUnloadEventListeners(this);
435 removeAllBeforeUnloadEventListeners(this);
436
437#if ENABLE(GAMEPAD)
438 if (m_gamepadEventListenerCount)
439 GamepadManager::singleton().unregisterDOMWindow(this);
440#endif
441
442 removeLanguageChangeObserver(this);
443}

462
463void DOMWindow::willDestroyCachedFrame()
464{
465 // It is necessary to copy m_observers to a separate vector because the Observer may
466 // unregister themselves from the DOMWindow as a result of the call to willDestroyGlobalObjectInCachedFrame.
467 for (auto* observer : copyToVector(m_observers)) {
468 if (m_observers.contains(observer))
469 observer->willDestroyGlobalObjectInCachedFrame();
470 }
471}
472
473void DOMWindow::willDestroyDocumentInFrame()
474{
475 // It is necessary to copy m_observers to a separate vector because the Observer may
476 // unregister themselves from the DOMWindow as a result of the call to willDestroyGlobalObjectInFrame.
477 for (auto* observer : copyToVector(m_observers)) {
478 if (m_observers.contains(observer))
479 observer->willDestroyGlobalObjectInFrame();
480 }
481}
482
483void DOMWindow::willDetachDocumentFromFrame()
484{
485 if (!frame())
486 return;
487
488 RELEASE_ASSERT(!m_isSuspendingObservers);
489
490 // It is necessary to copy m_observers to a separate vector because the Observer may
491 // unregister themselves from the DOMWindow as a result of the call to willDetachGlobalObjectFromFrame.
492 for (auto& observer : copyToVector(m_observers)) {
493 if (m_observers.contains(observer))
494 observer->willDetachGlobalObjectFromFrame();
495 }
496
497 if (m_performance)
498 m_performance->clearResourceTimings();
499
500 JSDOMWindowBase::fireFrameClearedWatchpointsForWindow(this);
501 InspectorInstrumentation::frameWindowDiscarded(*frame(), this);
502}

532void DOMWindow::resetUnlessSuspendedForDocumentSuspension()

534 if (m_suspendedForDocumentSuspension)
535 return;
536 willDestroyDocumentInFrame();
537}
538
539void DOMWindow::suspendForBackForwardCache()
540{
541 SetForScope<bool> isSuspendingObservers(m_isSuspendingObservers, true);
542 RELEASE_ASSERT(frame());
543
544 for (auto* observer : copyToVector(m_observers)) {
545 if (m_observers.contains(observer))
546 observer->suspendForBackForwardCache();
547 }
548 RELEASE_ASSERT(frame());
549
550 m_suspendedForDocumentSuspension = true;
551}
552
553void DOMWindow::resumeFromBackForwardCache()
554{
555 for (auto* observer : copyToVector(m_observers)) {
556 if (m_observers.contains(observer))
557 observer->resumeFromBackForwardCache();
558 }
559
560 m_suspendedForDocumentSuspension = false;
561}

576static ExceptionOr<SelectorQuery&> selectorQueryInFrame(Frame* frame, const String& selectors)
577{
578 if (!frame)
579 return Exception { NotSupportedError };
580
581 Document* document = frame->document();
582 if (!document)
583 return Exception { NotSupportedError };
584
585 return document->selectorQueryForString(selectors);
586}
587
588ExceptionOr<Ref<NodeList>> DOMWindow::collectMatchingElementsInFlatTree(Node& scope, const String& selectors)
589{
590 auto queryOrException = selectorQueryInFrame(frame(), selectors);
591 if (queryOrException.hasException())
592 return queryOrException.releaseException();
593
594 if (!is<ContainerNode>(scope))
595 return Ref<NodeList> { StaticElementList::create() };
596
597 SelectorQuery& query = queryOrException.releaseReturnValue();
598
599 Vector<Ref<Element>> result;
600 for (auto& node : composedTreeDescendants(downcast<ContainerNode>(scope))) {
601 if (is<Element>(node) && query.matches(downcast<Element>(node)) && !node.isInUserAgentShadowTree())
602 result.append(downcast<Element>(node));
603 }
604
605 return Ref<NodeList> { StaticElementList::create(WTFMove(result)) };
606}
607
608ExceptionOr<RefPtr<Element>> DOMWindow::matchingElementInFlatTree(Node& scope, const String& selectors)
609{
610 auto queryOrException = selectorQueryInFrame(frame(), selectors);
611 if (queryOrException.hasException())
612 return queryOrException.releaseException();
613
614 if (!is<ContainerNode>(scope))
615 return RefPtr<Element> { nullptr };
616
617 SelectorQuery& query = queryOrException.releaseReturnValue();
618
619 for (auto& node : composedTreeDescendants(downcast<ContainerNode>(scope))) {
620 if (is<Element>(node) && query.matches(downcast<Element>(node)) && !node.isInUserAgentShadowTree())
621 return &downcast<Element>(node);
622 }
623
624 return RefPtr<Element> { nullptr };
625}

729Performance& DOMWindow::performance() const
730{
731 if (!m_performance) {
732 auto* documentLoader = document() ? document()->loader() : nullptr;
733 auto timeOrigin = documentLoader ? documentLoader->timing().timeOrigin() : MonotonicTime::now();
734 m_performance = Performance::create(document(), timeOrigin);
735 }
736 ASSERT(m_performance->scriptExecutionContext() == document());
737 return *m_performance;
738}

774#if ENABLE(USER_MESSAGE_HANDLERS)
775
776bool DOMWindow::shouldHaveWebKitNamespaceForWorld(DOMWrapperWorld& world)
777{
778 auto* frame = this->frame();
779 if (!frame)
780 return false;
781
782 auto* page = frame->page();
783 if (!page)
784 return false;
785
786 bool hasUserMessageHandler = false;
787 page->userContentProvider().forEachUserMessageHandler([&](const UserMessageHandlerDescriptor& descriptor) {
788 if (&descriptor.world() == &world) {
789 hasUserMessageHandler = true;
790 return;
791 }
792 });
793
794 return hasUserMessageHandler;
795}
796
797WebKitNamespace* DOMWindow::webkitNamespace()
798{
799 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
800 return nullptr;
801 auto* page = frame()->page();
802 if (!page)
803 return nullptr;
804 if (!m_webkitNamespace)
805 m_webkitNamespace = WebKitNamespace::create(*this, page->userContentProvider());
806 return m_webkitNamespace.get();
807}
808
809#endif

811ExceptionOr<Storage*> DOMWindow::sessionStorage()
812{
813 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
814 return nullptr;
815
816 auto* document = this->document();
817 if (!document)
818 return nullptr;
819
820 if (!document->securityOrigin().canAccessSessionStorage(document->topOrigin()))
821 return Exception { SecurityError };
822
823 if (m_sessionStorage)
824 return m_sessionStorage.get();
825
826 auto* page = document->page();
827 if (!page)
828 return nullptr;
829
830 auto storageArea = page->sessionStorage()->storageArea(document->securityOrigin().data());
831 m_sessionStorage = Storage::create(*this, WTFMove(storageArea));
832 return m_sessionStorage.get();
833}

835ExceptionOr<Storage*> DOMWindow::localStorage()
836{
837 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
838 return nullptr;
839
840 auto* document = this->document();
841 if (!document)
842 return nullptr;
843
844 if (!document->securityOrigin().canAccessLocalStorage(nullptr))
845 return Exception { SecurityError };
846
847 auto* page = document->page();
848 // FIXME: We should consider supporting access/modification to local storage
849 // after calling window.close(). See <https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=135330>.
850 if (!page || !page->isClosing()) {
851 if (m_localStorage)
852 return m_localStorage.get();
853 }
854
855 if (!page)
856 return nullptr;
857
858 if (page->isClosing())
859 return nullptr;
860
861 if (!page->settings().localStorageEnabled())
862 return nullptr;
863
864 auto storageArea = page->storageNamespaceProvider().localStorageArea(*document);
865 m_localStorage = Storage::create(*this, WTFMove(storageArea));
866 return m_localStorage.get();
867}
868
869ExceptionOr<void> DOMWindow::postMessage(JSC::JSGlobalObject& lexicalGlobalObject, DOMWindow& incumbentWindow, JSC::JSValue messageValue, WindowPostMessageOptions&& options)
870{
871 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
872 return { };
873
874 Document* sourceDocument = incumbentWindow.document();
875
876 // Compute the target origin. We need to do this synchronously in order
877 // to generate the SyntaxError exception correctly.
878 RefPtr<SecurityOrigin> target;
879 if (options.targetOrigin == "/") {
880 if (!sourceDocument)
881 return { };
882 target = &sourceDocument->securityOrigin();
883 } else if (options.targetOrigin != "*") {
884 target = SecurityOrigin::createFromString(options.targetOrigin);
885 // It doesn't make sense target a postMessage at a unique origin
886 // because there's no way to represent a unique origin in a string.
887 if (target->isUnique())
888 return Exception { SyntaxError };
889 }
890
891 Vector<RefPtr<MessagePort>> ports;
892 auto messageData = SerializedScriptValue::create(lexicalGlobalObject, messageValue, WTFMove(options.transfer), ports, SerializationContext::WindowPostMessage);
893 if (messageData.hasException())
894 return messageData.releaseException();
895
896 auto disentangledPorts = MessagePort::disentanglePorts(WTFMove(ports));
897 if (disentangledPorts.hasException())
898 return disentangledPorts.releaseException();
899
900 // Capture the source of the message. We need to do this synchronously
901 // in order to capture the source of the message correctly.
902 if (!sourceDocument)
903 return { };
904 auto sourceOrigin = sourceDocument->securityOrigin().toString();
905
906 // Capture stack trace only when inspector front-end is loaded as it may be time consuming.
907 RefPtr<ScriptCallStack> stackTrace;
908 if (InspectorInstrumentation::consoleAgentEnabled(sourceDocument))
909 stackTrace = createScriptCallStack(JSExecState::currentState());
910
911 auto postMessageIdentifier = InspectorInstrumentation::willPostMessage(*frame());
912
913 MessageWithMessagePorts message { messageData.releaseReturnValue(), disentangledPorts.releaseReturnValue() };
914
915 // Schedule the message.
916 RefPtr<WindowProxy> incumbentWindowProxy = incumbentWindow.frame() ? &incumbentWindow.frame()->windowProxy() : nullptr;
917 auto userGestureToForward = UserGestureIndicator::currentUserGesture();
918
919 document()->eventLoop().queueTask(TaskSource::PostedMessageQueue, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), message = WTFMove(message), incumbentWindowProxy = WTFMove(incumbentWindowProxy), sourceOrigin = WTFMove(sourceOrigin), userGestureToForward = WTFMove(userGestureToForward), postMessageIdentifier, stackTrace = WTFMove(stackTrace), targetOrigin = WTFMove(target)]() mutable {
920 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
921 return;
922
923 Ref<Frame> frame = *this->frame();
924 if (targetOrigin) {
925 // Check target origin now since the target document may have changed since the timer was scheduled.
926 if (!targetOrigin->isSameSchemeHostPort(document()->securityOrigin())) {
927 if (auto* pageConsole = console()) {
928 auto message = makeString("Unable to post message to ", targetOrigin->toString(), ". Recipient has origin ", document()->securityOrigin().toString(), ".\n");
929 if (stackTrace)
930 pageConsole->addMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, message, *stackTrace);
931 else
932 pageConsole->addMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, message);
933 }
934
935 InspectorInstrumentation::didFailPostMessage(frame, postMessageIdentifier);
936 return;
937 }
938 }
939
940 UserGestureIndicator userGestureIndicator(userGestureToForward);
941 InspectorInstrumentation::willDispatchPostMessage(frame, postMessageIdentifier);
942
943 auto event = MessageEvent::create(MessagePort::entanglePorts(*document(), WTFMove(message.transferredPorts)), message.message.releaseNonNull(), sourceOrigin, { }, incumbentWindowProxy ? std::make_optional(MessageEventSource(WTFMove(incumbentWindowProxy))) : std::nullopt);
944 dispatchEvent(event);
945
946 InspectorInstrumentation::didDispatchPostMessage(frame, postMessageIdentifier);
947 });
948
949 InspectorInstrumentation::didPostMessage(*frame(), postMessageIdentifier, lexicalGlobalObject);
950
951 return { };
952}

979void DOMWindow::focus(bool allowFocus)
980{
981 if (!frame())
982 return;
983
984 auto protectedFrame = makeRefPtr(frame());
985
986 Page* page = protectedFrame->page();
987 if (!page)
988 return;
989
990 allowFocus = allowFocus || WindowFocusAllowedIndicator::windowFocusAllowed() || !protectedFrame->settings().windowFocusRestricted();
991
992 // If we're a top level window, bring the window to the front.
993 if (protectedFrame->isMainFrame() && allowFocus)
994 page->chrome().focus();
995
996 if (!protectedFrame->hasHadUserInteraction() && !isSameSecurityOriginAsMainFrame())
997 return;
998
999 // Clear the current frame's focused node if a new frame is about to be focused.
1000 auto focusedFrame = makeRefPtr(page->focusController().focusedFrame());
1001 if (focusedFrame && focusedFrame != protectedFrame)
1002 focusedFrame->document()->setFocusedElement(nullptr);
1003
1004 protectedFrame->eventHandler().focusDocumentView();
1005}

1033void DOMWindow::close()
1034{
1035 auto* frame = this->frame();
1036 if (!frame)
1037 return;
1038
1039 Page* page = frame->page();
1040 if (!page)
1041 return;
1042
1043 if (!frame->isMainFrame())
1044 return;
1045
1046 if (!(page->openedByDOM() || page->backForward().count() <= 1)) {
1047 console()->addMessage(MessageSource::JS, MessageLevel::Warning, "Can't close the window since it was not opened by JavaScript"_s);
1048 return;
1049 }
1050
1051 if (!frame->loader().shouldClose())
1052 return;
1053
1054 ResourceLoadObserver::shared().updateCentralStatisticsStore([] { });
1055
1056 page->setIsClosing();
1057 page->chrome().closeWindowSoon();
1058}

1060void DOMWindow::print()
1061{
1062 auto* frame = this->frame();
1063 if (!frame)
1064 return;
1065
1066 auto* page = frame->page();
1067 if (!page)
1068 return;
1069
1070 if (!page->arePromptsAllowed()) {
1071 printErrorMessage("Use of window.print is not allowed while unloading a page.");
1072 return;
1073 }
1074
1075 if (page->isControlledByAutomation())
1076 return;
1077
1078 if (auto loader = frame->loader().activeDocumentLoader(); loader && loader->isLoading()) {
1079 m_shouldPrintWhenFinishedLoading = true;
1080 return;
1081 }
1082 m_shouldPrintWhenFinishedLoading = false;
1083 page->chrome().print(*frame);
1084}

1200bool DOMWindow::find(const String& string, bool caseSensitive, bool backwards, bool wrap, bool /*wholeWord*/, bool /*searchInFrames*/, bool /*showDialog*/) const
1201{
1202 // SearchBuffer allocates memory much larger than the searched string, so it's necessary to limit its length.
1203 // Most searches are for a phrase or a paragraph, so an upper limit of 64kB is more than enough in practice.
1204 constexpr auto maximumStringLength = std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max();
1205 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame() || string.length() > maximumStringLength)
1206 return false;
1207
1208 // FIXME (13016): Support wholeWord, searchInFrames and showDialog.
1209 FindOptions options { DoNotTraverseFlatTree };
1210 if (backwards)
1211 options.add(Backwards);
1212 if (!caseSensitive)
1213 options.add(CaseInsensitive);
1214 if (wrap)
1215 options.add(WrapAround);
1216 return frame()->editor().findString(string, options);
1217}

1523void DOMWindow::overrideTransientActivationDurationForTesting(std::optional<Seconds>&& override)
1524{
1525 transientActivationDurationOverrideForTesting() = WTFMove(override);
1526}
1527
1528// When the current high resolution time is greater than or equal to the last activation timestamp in W, and
1529// less than the last activation timestamp in W plus the transient activation duration, then W is said to
1530// have transient activation. (https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/interaction.html#transient-activation)
1531bool DOMWindow::hasTransientActivation() const
1532{
1533 auto now = MonotonicTime::now();
1534 return now >= m_lastActivationTimestamp && now < (m_lastActivationTimestamp + transientActivationDuration());
1535}
1536
1537// https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/interaction.html#consume-user-activation
1538bool DOMWindow::consumeTransientActivation()
1539{
1540 if (!hasTransientActivation())
1541 return false;
1542
1543 for (Frame* frame = this->frame() ? &this->frame()->tree().top() : nullptr; frame; frame = frame->tree().traverseNext()) {
1544 auto* window = frame->window();
1545 if (!window || window->lastActivationTimestamp() != MonotonicTime::infinity())
1546 window->setLastActivationTimestamp(-MonotonicTime::infinity());
1547 }
1548
1549 return true;
1550}
1551
1552// https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/interaction.html#activation-notification
1553void DOMWindow::notifyActivated(MonotonicTime activationTime)
1554{
1555 setLastActivationTimestamp(activationTime);
1556 if (!frame())
1557 return;
1558
1559 for (Frame* ancestor = frame() ? frame()->tree().parent() : nullptr; ancestor; ancestor = ancestor->tree().parent()) {
1560 if (auto* window = ancestor->window())
1561 window->setLastActivationTimestamp(activationTime);
1562 }
1563
1564 auto* securityOrigin = this->securityOrigin();
1565 if (!securityOrigin)
1566 return;
1567
1568 auto* descendant = frame();
1569 while ((descendant = descendant->tree().traverseNext(frame()))) {
1570 auto* descendantWindow = descendant->window();
1571 if (!descendantWindow)
1572 continue;
1573
1574 auto* descendantSecurityOrigin = descendantWindow->securityOrigin();
1575 if (!descendantSecurityOrigin || !descendantSecurityOrigin->isSameOriginAs(*securityOrigin))
1576 continue;
1577
1578 descendantWindow->setLastActivationTimestamp(activationTime);
1579 }
1580}

1594RefPtr<CSSRuleList> DOMWindow::getMatchedCSSRules(Element* element, const String& pseudoElement, bool authorOnly) const
1595{
1596 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
1597 return nullptr;
1598
1599 unsigned colonStart = pseudoElement[0] == ':' ? (pseudoElement[1] == ':' ? 2 : 1) : 0;
1600 auto pseudoType = CSSSelector::parsePseudoElementType(StringView { pseudoElement }.substring(colonStart));
1601 if (pseudoType == CSSSelector::PseudoElementUnknown && !pseudoElement.isEmpty())
1602 return nullptr;
1603
1604 auto* frame = this->frame();
1605 frame->document()->styleScope().flushPendingUpdate();
1606
1607 unsigned rulesToInclude = Style::Resolver::AuthorCSSRules;
1608 if (!authorOnly)
1609 rulesToInclude |= Style::Resolver::UAAndUserCSSRules;
1610
1611 PseudoId pseudoId = CSSSelector::pseudoId(pseudoType);
1612
1613 auto matchedRules = frame->document()->styleScope().resolver().pseudoStyleRulesForElement(element, pseudoId, rulesToInclude);
1614 if (matchedRules.isEmpty())
1615 return nullptr;
1616
1617 bool allowCrossOrigin = frame->settings().crossOriginCheckInGetMatchedCSSRulesDisabled();
1618
1619 auto ruleList = StaticCSSRuleList::create();
1620 for (auto& rule : matchedRules) {
1621 if (!allowCrossOrigin && !rule->hasDocumentSecurityOrigin())
1622 continue;
1623 ruleList->rules().append(rule->createCSSOMWrapper());
1624 }
1625
1626 if (ruleList->rules().isEmpty())
1627 return nullptr;
1628
1629 return ruleList;
1630}

1679
1680void DOMWindow::scrollBy(const ScrollToOptions& options) const
1681{
1682 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
1683 return;
1684
1685 document()->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1686
1687 auto* frame = this->frame();
1688 if (!frame)
1689 return;
1690
1691 auto view = makeRefPtr(frame->view());
1692 if (!view)
1693 return;
1694
1695 ScrollToOptions scrollToOptions = normalizeNonFiniteCoordinatesOrFallBackTo(options, 0, 0);
1696 scrollToOptions.left.value() += view->mapFromLayoutToCSSUnits(view->contentsScrollPosition().x());
1697 scrollToOptions.top.value() += view->mapFromLayoutToCSSUnits(view->contentsScrollPosition().y());
1698 scrollTo(scrollToOptions, ScrollClamping::Clamped, ScrollSnapPointSelectionMethod::Directional);
1699}
1700
1701void DOMWindow::scrollTo(double x, double y, ScrollClamping clamping) const
1702{
1703 scrollTo(ScrollToOptions(x, y), clamping);
1704}
1705
1706void DOMWindow::scrollTo(const ScrollToOptions& options, ScrollClamping clamping, ScrollSnapPointSelectionMethod snapPointSelectionMethod) const
1707{
1708 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
1709 return;
1710
1711 RefPtr<FrameView> view = frame()->view();
1712 if (!view)
1713 return;
1714
1715 ScrollToOptions scrollToOptions = normalizeNonFiniteCoordinatesOrFallBackTo(options,
1716 view->contentsScrollPosition().x(), view->contentsScrollPosition().y()
1717 );
1718
1719 // This is an optimization for the common case of scrolling to (0, 0) when the scroller is already at the origin.
1720 // If an animated scroll is in progress, this optimization is skipped to ensure that the animated scroll is really stopped.
1721 if (view->currentScrollBehaviorStatus() == ScrollBehaviorStatus::NotInAnimation && !scrollToOptions.left.value() && !scrollToOptions.top.value() && view->contentsScrollPosition() == IntPoint(0, 0))
1722 return;
1723
1724 document()->updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1725
1726 IntPoint layoutPos(view->mapFromCSSToLayoutUnits(scrollToOptions.left.value()), view->mapFromCSSToLayoutUnits(scrollToOptions.top.value()));
1727
1728 // FIXME: Should we use document()->scrollingElement()?
1729 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=205059
1730 auto animated = useSmoothScrolling(scrollToOptions.behavior.value_or(ScrollBehavior::Auto), document()->documentElement()) ? AnimatedScroll::Yes : AnimatedScroll::No;
1731 auto scrollPositionChangeOptions = ScrollPositionChangeOptions::createProgrammaticWithOptions(clamping, animated, snapPointSelectionMethod);
1732 view->setContentsScrollPosition(layoutPos, scrollPositionChangeOptions);
1733}

1930bool DOMWindow::isSameSecurityOriginAsMainFrame() const
1931{
1932 auto* frame = this->frame();
1933 if (!frame || !frame->page() || !document())
1934 return false;
1935
1936 if (frame->isMainFrame())
1937 return true;
1938
1939 Document* mainFrameDocument = frame->mainFrame().document();
1940
1941 if (mainFrameDocument && document()->securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(mainFrameDocument->securityOrigin()))
1942 return true;
1943
1944 return false;
1945}
1946
1947bool DOMWindow::addEventListener(const AtomString& eventType, Ref<EventListener>&& listener, const AddEventListenerOptions& options)
1948{
1949 if (!EventTarget::addEventListener(eventType, WTFMove(listener), options))
1950 return false;
1951
1952 auto* document = this->document();
1953 if (document) {
1954 document->addListenerTypeIfNeeded(eventType);
1955 if (eventNames().isWheelEventType(eventType))
1956 document->didAddWheelEventHandler(*document);
1957 else if (eventNames().isTouchRelatedEventType(eventType, *document))
1958 document->didAddTouchEventHandler(*document);
1959 else if (eventType == eventNames().storageEvent)
1960 didAddStorageEventListener(*this);
1961 }
1962
1963 if (eventType == eventNames().unloadEvent)
1964 addUnloadEventListener(this);
1965 else if (eventType == eventNames().beforeunloadEvent && allowsBeforeUnloadListeners(this))
1966 addBeforeUnloadEventListener(this);
1967#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1968 else if (eventType == eventNames().scrollEvent)
1969 incrementScrollEventListenersCount();
1970#endif
1971#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
1972 else if (document && eventNames().isTouchRelatedEventType(eventType, *document))
1973 ++m_touchAndGestureEventListenerCount;
1974#endif
1975#if ENABLE(IOS_GESTURE_EVENTS)
1976 else if (eventNames().isGestureEventType(eventType))
1977 ++m_touchAndGestureEventListenerCount;
1978#endif
1979#if ENABLE(GAMEPAD)
1980 else if (eventNames().isGamepadEventType(eventType))
1981 incrementGamepadEventListenerCount();
1982#endif
1983#if ENABLE(DEVICE_ORIENTATION)
1984 else if (eventType == eventNames().deviceorientationEvent)
1985 startListeningForDeviceOrientationIfNecessary();
1986 else if (eventType == eventNames().devicemotionEvent)
1987 startListeningForDeviceMotionIfNecessary();
1988#endif
1989
1990 return true;
1991}

2191bool DOMWindow::removeEventListener(const AtomString& eventType, EventListener& listener, const EventListenerOptions& options)
2192{
2193 if (!EventTarget::removeEventListener(eventType, listener, options.capture))
2194 return false;
2195
2196 auto* document = this->document();
2197 if (document) {
2198 if (eventNames().isWheelEventType(eventType))
2199 document->didRemoveWheelEventHandler(*document);
2200 else if (eventNames().isTouchRelatedEventType(eventType, *document))
2201 document->didRemoveTouchEventHandler(*document);
2202 }
2203
2204 if (eventType == eventNames().unloadEvent)
2205 removeUnloadEventListener(this);
2206 else if (eventType == eventNames().beforeunloadEvent && allowsBeforeUnloadListeners(this))
2207 removeBeforeUnloadEventListener(this);
2208#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2209 else if (eventType == eventNames().scrollEvent)
2210 decrementScrollEventListenersCount();
2211#endif
2212#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
2213 else if (document && eventNames().isTouchRelatedEventType(eventType, *document)) {
2214 ASSERT(m_touchAndGestureEventListenerCount > 0);
2215 --m_touchAndGestureEventListenerCount;
2216 }
2217#endif
2218#if ENABLE(IOS_GESTURE_EVENTS)
2219 else if (eventNames().isGestureEventType(eventType)) {
2220 ASSERT(m_touchAndGestureEventListenerCount > 0);
2221 --m_touchAndGestureEventListenerCount;
2222 }
2223#endif
2224#if ENABLE(GAMEPAD)
2225 else if (eventNames().isGamepadEventType(eventType))
2226 decrementGamepadEventListenerCount();
2227#endif
2228#if ENABLE(DEVICE_ORIENTATION)
2229 else if (eventType == eventNames().deviceorientationEvent)
2230 stopListeningForDeviceOrientationIfNecessary();
2231 else if (eventType == eventNames().devicemotionEvent)
2232 stopListeningForDeviceMotionIfNecessary();
2233#endif
2234
2235 return true;
2236}

2245void DOMWindow::dispatchLoadEvent()
2246{
2247 // If we did not protect it, the document loader and its timing subobject might get destroyed
2248 // as a side effect of what event handling code does.
2249 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
2250 auto protectedLoader = makeRefPtr(frame() ? frame()->loader().documentLoader() : nullptr);
2251 bool shouldMarkLoadEventTimes = protectedLoader && !protectedLoader->timing().loadEventStart();
2252
2253 if (shouldMarkLoadEventTimes)
2254 protectedLoader->timing().markLoadEventStart();
2255
2256 dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().loadEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No), document());
2257
2258 if (shouldMarkLoadEventTimes)
2259 protectedLoader->timing().markLoadEventEnd();
2260
2261 // Send a separate load event to the element that owns this frame.
2262 if (frame()) {
2263 if (auto* owner = frame()->ownerElement())
2264 owner->dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().loadEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
2265 }
2266
2267 InspectorInstrumentation::loadEventFired(frame());
2268}
2269
2270void DOMWindow::dispatchEvent(Event& event, EventTarget* target)
2271{
2272 // FIXME: It's confusing to have both the inherited EventTarget::dispatchEvent function
2273 // and this function, which does something nearly identical but subtly different if
2274 // called with a target of null. Most callers pass the document as the target, though.
2275 // Fixing this could allow us to remove the special case in DocumentEventQueue::dispatchEvent.
2276
2277 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
2278
2279 // Pausing a page may trigger pagehide and pageshow events. WebCore also implicitly fires these
2280 // events when closing a WebView. Here we keep track of the state of the page to prevent duplicate,
2281 // unbalanced events per the definition of the pageshow event:
2282 // <http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/multipage/history.html#event-pageshow>.
2283 // FIXME: This code should go at call sites where pageshowEvent and pagehideEvents are
2284 // generated, not here inside the event dispatching process.
2285 if (event.eventInterface() == PageTransitionEventInterfaceType) {
2286 if (event.type() == eventNames().pageshowEvent) {
2287 if (m_lastPageStatus == PageStatus::Shown)
2288 return; // Event was previously dispatched; do not fire a duplicate event.
2289 m_lastPageStatus = PageStatus::Shown;
2290 } else if (event.type() == eventNames().pagehideEvent) {
2291 if (m_lastPageStatus == PageStatus::Hidden)
2292 return; // Event was previously dispatched; do not fire a duplicate event.
2293 m_lastPageStatus = PageStatus::Hidden;
2294 }
2295 }
2296
2297 // FIXME: It doesn't seem right to have the inspector instrumentation here since not all
2298 // events dispatched to the window object are guaranteed to flow through this function.
2299 // But the instrumentation prevents us from calling EventDispatcher::dispatchEvent here.
2300 event.setTarget(target ? target : this);
2301 event.setCurrentTarget(this);
2302 event.setEventPhase(Event::AT_TARGET);
2303 event.resetBeforeDispatch();
2304
2305 Frame* protectedFrame = nullptr;
2306 bool hasListenersForEvent = false;
2307 if (UNLIKELY(InspectorInstrumentation::hasFrontends())) {
2308 protectedFrame = frame();
2309 hasListenersForEvent = hasEventListeners(event.type());
2310 if (hasListenersForEvent)
2311 InspectorInstrumentation::willDispatchEventOnWindow(protectedFrame, event, *this);
2312 }
2313
2314 // FIXME: We should use EventDispatcher everywhere.
2315 fireEventListeners(event, EventInvokePhase::Capturing);
2316 fireEventListeners(event, EventInvokePhase::Bubbling);
2317
2318 if (hasListenersForEvent)
2319 InspectorInstrumentation::didDispatchEventOnWindow(protectedFrame, event);
2320
2321 event.resetAfterDispatch();
2322}

2377void DOMWindow::setLocation(DOMWindow& activeWindow, const URL& completedURL, SetLocationLocking locking)
2378{
2379 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
2380 return;
2381
2382 Document* activeDocument = activeWindow.document();
2383 if (!activeDocument)
2384 return;
2385
2386 auto* frame = this->frame();

2389
2390 if (isInsecureScriptAccess(activeWindow, completedURL.string()))

2393 // We want a new history item if we are processing a user gesture.
2394 LockHistory lockHistory = (locking != LockHistoryBasedOnGestureState || !UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGesture()) ? LockHistory::Yes : LockHistory::No;
2395 LockBackForwardList lockBackForwardList = (locking != LockHistoryBasedOnGestureState) ? LockBackForwardList::Yes : LockBackForwardList::No;
2396 frame->navigationScheduler().scheduleLocationChange(*activeDocument, activeDocument->securityOrigin(),
2397 // FIXME: What if activeDocument()->frame() is 0?
2398 completedURL, activeDocument->frame()->loader().outgoingReferrer(),
2399 lockHistory, lockBackForwardList);

2411String DOMWindow::crossDomainAccessErrorMessage(const DOMWindow& activeWindow, IncludeTargetOrigin includeTargetOrigin)
2412{
2413 const URL& activeWindowURL = activeWindow.document()->url();
2414 if (activeWindowURL.isNull())
2415 return String();
2416
2417 ASSERT(!activeWindow.document()->securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(document()->securityOrigin()));
2418
2419 // FIXME: This message, and other console messages, have extra newlines. Should remove them.
2420 SecurityOrigin& activeOrigin = activeWindow.document()->securityOrigin();
2421 SecurityOrigin& targetOrigin = document()->securityOrigin();
2422 String message;
2423 if (includeTargetOrigin == IncludeTargetOrigin::Yes)
2424 message = makeString("Blocked a frame with origin \"", activeOrigin.toString(), "\" from accessing a frame with origin \"", targetOrigin.toString(), "\". ");
2425 else
2426 message = makeString("Blocked a frame with origin \"", activeOrigin.toString(), "\" from accessing a cross-origin frame. ");
2427
2428 // Sandbox errors: Use the origin of the frames' location, rather than their actual origin (since we know that at least one will be "null").
2429 URL activeURL = activeWindow.document()->url();
2430 URL targetURL = document()->url();
2431 if (document()->isSandboxed(SandboxOrigin) || activeWindow.document()->isSandboxed(SandboxOrigin)) {
2432 if (includeTargetOrigin == IncludeTargetOrigin::Yes)
2433 message = makeString("Blocked a frame at \"", SecurityOrigin::create(activeURL).get().toString(), "\" from accessing a frame at \"", SecurityOrigin::create(targetURL).get().toString(), "\". ");
2434 else
2435 message = makeString("Blocked a frame at \"", SecurityOrigin::create(activeURL).get().toString(), "\" from accessing a cross-origin frame. ");
2436
2437 if (document()->isSandboxed(SandboxOrigin) && activeWindow.document()->isSandboxed(SandboxOrigin))
2438 return makeString("Sandbox access violation: ", message, " Both frames are sandboxed and lack the \"allow-same-origin\" flag.");
2439 if (document()->isSandboxed(SandboxOrigin))
2440 return makeString("Sandbox access violation: ", message, " The frame being accessed is sandboxed and lacks the \"allow-same-origin\" flag.");
2441 return makeString("Sandbox access violation: ", message, " The frame requesting access is sandboxed and lacks the \"allow-same-origin\" flag.");
2442 }
2443
2444 if (includeTargetOrigin == IncludeTargetOrigin::Yes) {
2445 // Protocol errors: Use the URL's protocol rather than the origin's protocol so that we get a useful message for non-heirarchal URLs like 'data:'.
2446 if (targetOrigin.protocol() != activeOrigin.protocol())
2447 return message + " The frame requesting access has a protocol of \"" + activeURL.protocol() + "\", the frame being accessed has a protocol of \"" + targetURL.protocol() + "\". Protocols must match.\n";
2448
2449 // 'document.domain' errors.
2450 if (targetOrigin.domainWasSetInDOM() && activeOrigin.domainWasSetInDOM())
2451 return message + "The frame requesting access set \"document.domain\" to \"" + activeOrigin.domain() + "\", the frame being accessed set it to \"" + targetOrigin.domain() + "\". Both must set \"document.domain\" to the same value to allow access.";
2452 if (activeOrigin.domainWasSetInDOM())
2453 return message + "The frame requesting access set \"document.domain\" to \"" + activeOrigin.domain() + "\", but the frame being accessed did not. Both must set \"document.domain\" to the same value to allow access.";
2454 if (targetOrigin.domainWasSetInDOM())
2455 return message + "The frame being accessed set \"document.domain\" to \"" + targetOrigin.domain() + "\", but the frame requesting access did not. Both must set \"document.domain\" to the same value to allow access.";
2456 }
2457
2458 // Default.
2459 return message + "Protocols, domains, and ports must match.";
2460}

2462bool DOMWindow::isInsecureScriptAccess(DOMWindow& activeWindow, const String& urlString)
2463{
2464 if (!WTF::protocolIsJavaScript(urlString))
2465 return false;
2466
2467 // If this DOMWindow isn't currently active in the Frame, then there's no
2468 // way we should allow the access.
2469 // FIXME: Remove this check if we're able to disconnect DOMWindow from
2470 // Frame on navigation: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=62054
2471 if (isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame()) {
2472 // FIXME: Is there some way to eliminate the need for a separate "activeWindow == this" check?
2473 if (&activeWindow == this)
2474 return false;
2475
2476 // FIXME: The name canAccess seems to be a roundabout way to ask "can execute script".
2477 // Can we name the SecurityOrigin function better to make this more clear?
2478 if (activeWindow.document()->securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(document()->securityOrigin()))
2479 return false;
2480 }
2481
2482 printErrorMessage(crossDomainAccessErrorMessage(activeWindow, IncludeTargetOrigin::Yes));
2483 return true;
2484}

2486ExceptionOr<RefPtr<Frame>> DOMWindow::createWindow(const String& urlString, const AtomString& frameName, const WindowFeatures& windowFeatures, DOMWindow& activeWindow, Frame& firstFrame, Frame& openerFrame, const WTF::Function<void(DOMWindow&)>& prepareDialogFunction)
2487{
2488 Frame* activeFrame = activeWindow.frame();
2489 if (!activeFrame)
2490 return RefPtr<Frame> { nullptr };
2491
2492 Document* activeDocument = activeWindow.document();
2493 if (!activeDocument)
2494 return RefPtr<Frame> { nullptr };
2495
2496 URL completedURL = urlString.isEmpty() ? URL({ }, emptyString()) : firstFrame.document()->completeURL(urlString);
2497 if (!completedURL.isEmpty() && !completedURL.isValid())
2498 return Exception { SyntaxError };
2499
2500 // For whatever reason, Firefox uses the first frame to determine the outgoingReferrer. We replicate that behavior here.
2501 String referrer = windowFeatures.noreferrer ? String() : SecurityPolicy::generateReferrerHeader(firstFrame.document()->referrerPolicy(), completedURL, firstFrame.loader().outgoingReferrer());
2502 auto initiatedByMainFrame = activeFrame->isMainFrame() ? InitiatedByMainFrame::Yes : InitiatedByMainFrame::Unknown;
2503
2504 ResourceRequest resourceRequest { completedURL, referrer };
2505 FrameLoadRequest frameLoadRequest { *activeDocument, activeDocument->securityOrigin(), WTFMove(resourceRequest), frameName, initiatedByMainFrame };
2506 frameLoadRequest.setShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy(activeDocument->shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToPropagate());
2507
2508 // We pass the opener frame for the lookupFrame in case the active frame is different from
2509 // the opener frame, and the name references a frame relative to the opener frame.
2510 bool created;
2511 auto newFrame = WebCore::createWindow(*activeFrame, openerFrame, WTFMove(frameLoadRequest), windowFeatures, created);
2512 if (!newFrame)
2513 return RefPtr<Frame> { nullptr };
2514
2515 bool noopener = windowFeatures.noopener || windowFeatures.noreferrer;
2516 if (!noopener)
2517 newFrame->loader().setOpener(&openerFrame);
2518
2519 if (created)
2520 newFrame->page()->setOpenedByDOM();
2521
2522 if (newFrame->document()->domWindow()->isInsecureScriptAccess(activeWindow, completedURL.string()))
2523 return noopener ? RefPtr<Frame> { nullptr } : newFrame;
2524
2525 if (prepareDialogFunction)
2526 prepareDialogFunction(*newFrame->document()->domWindow());
2527
2528 if (created) {
2529 ResourceRequest resourceRequest { completedURL, referrer, ResourceRequestCachePolicy::UseProtocolCachePolicy };
2530 FrameLoader::addSameSiteInfoToRequestIfNeeded(resourceRequest, openerFrame.document());
2531 FrameLoadRequest frameLoadRequest { *activeWindow.document(), activeWindow.document()->securityOrigin(), WTFMove(resourceRequest), "_self"_s, initiatedByMainFrame };
2532 frameLoadRequest.setShouldOpenExternalURLsPolicy(activeDocument->shouldOpenExternalURLsPolicyToPropagate());
2533 newFrame->loader().changeLocation(WTFMove(frameLoadRequest));
2534 } else if (!urlString.isEmpty()) {
2535 LockHistory lockHistory = UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGesture() ? LockHistory::No : LockHistory::Yes;
2536 newFrame->navigationScheduler().scheduleLocationChange(*activeDocument, activeDocument->securityOrigin(), completedURL, referrer, lockHistory, LockBackForwardList::No);
2537 }
2538
2539 // Navigating the new frame could result in it being detached from its page by a navigation policy delegate.
2540 if (!newFrame->page())
2541 return RefPtr<Frame> { nullptr };
2542
2543 return noopener ? RefPtr<Frame> { nullptr } : newFrame;
2544}

2546ExceptionOr<RefPtr<WindowProxy>> DOMWindow::open(DOMWindow& activeWindow, DOMWindow& firstWindow, const String& urlStringToOpen, const AtomString& frameName, const String& windowFeaturesString)
2547{
2548#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
2549 if (auto* document = this->document()) {
2550 if (document->settings().needsSiteSpecificQuirks() && urlStringToOpen == Quirks::BBCRadioPlayerURLString()) {
2551 auto radioPlayerDomain = RegistrableDomain(URL(URL(), Quirks::staticRadioPlayerURLString()));
2552 auto BBCDomain = RegistrableDomain(URL(URL(), Quirks::BBCRadioPlayerURLString()));
2553 if (!ResourceLoadObserver::shared().hasCrossPageStorageAccess(radioPlayerDomain, BBCDomain))
2554 return RefPtr<WindowProxy> { nullptr };
2555 }
2556 }
2557#endif
2558
2559 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
2560 return RefPtr<WindowProxy> { nullptr };
2561
2562 auto* activeDocument = activeWindow.document();
2563 if (!activeDocument)
2564 return RefPtr<WindowProxy> { nullptr };
2565
2566 auto* firstFrame = firstWindow.frame();
2567 if (!firstFrame)
2568 return RefPtr<WindowProxy> { nullptr };
2569
2570 auto urlString = urlStringToOpen;
2571 if (activeDocument->quirks().shouldOpenAsAboutBlank(urlStringToOpen))
2572 urlString = "about:blank"_s;
2573
2574#if ENABLE(CONTENT_EXTENSIONS)
2575 auto* page = firstFrame->page();
2576 auto* firstFrameDocument = firstFrame->document();
2577 auto* mainFrameDocument = firstFrame->mainFrame().document();
2578 auto* mainFrameDocumentLoader = mainFrameDocument ? mainFrameDocument->loader() : nullptr;
2579 if (firstFrameDocument && page && mainFrameDocumentLoader) {
2580 auto results = page->userContentProvider().processContentRuleListsForLoad(*page, firstFrameDocument->completeURL(urlString), ContentExtensions::ResourceType::Popup, *mainFrameDocumentLoader);
2581 if (results.summary.blockedLoad)
2582 return RefPtr<WindowProxy> { nullptr };
2583 }
2584#endif
2585
2586 auto* frame = this->frame();
2587 if (!frame)
2588 return RefPtr<WindowProxy> { nullptr };
2589
2590 if (!firstWindow.allowPopUp()) {
2591 // Because FrameTree::findFrameForNavigation() returns true for empty strings, we must check for empty frame names.
2592 // Otherwise, illegitimate window.open() calls with no name will pass right through the popup blocker.
2593 if (frameName.isEmpty() || !frame->loader().findFrameForNavigation(frameName, activeDocument))
2594 return RefPtr<WindowProxy> { nullptr };
2595 }
2596
2597 // Get the target frame for the special cases of _top and _parent.
2598 // In those cases, we schedule a location change right now and return early.
2599 Frame* targetFrame = nullptr;
2600 if (equalIgnoringASCIICase(frameName, "_top"))
2601 targetFrame = &frame->tree().top();
2602 else if (equalIgnoringASCIICase(frameName, "_parent")) {
2603 if (Frame* parent = frame->tree().parent())
2604 targetFrame = parent;
2605 else
2606 targetFrame = frame;
2607 }
2608 if (targetFrame) {
2609 if (!activeDocument->canNavigate(targetFrame))
2610 return RefPtr<WindowProxy> { nullptr };
2611
2612 URL completedURL = firstFrame->document()->completeURL(urlString);
2613
2614 if (targetFrame->document()->domWindow()->isInsecureScriptAccess(activeWindow, completedURL.string()))
2615 return &targetFrame->windowProxy();
2616
2617 if (urlString.isEmpty())
2618 return &targetFrame->windowProxy();
2619
2620 // For whatever reason, Firefox uses the first window rather than the active window to
2621 // determine the outgoing referrer. We replicate that behavior here.
2622 LockHistory lockHistory = UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGesture() ? LockHistory::No : LockHistory::Yes;
2623 targetFrame->navigationScheduler().scheduleLocationChange(*activeDocument, activeDocument->securityOrigin(), completedURL, firstFrame->loader().outgoingReferrer(),
2624 lockHistory, LockBackForwardList::No);
2625 return &targetFrame->windowProxy();
2626 }
2627
2628 auto newFrameOrException = createWindow(urlString, frameName, parseWindowFeatures(windowFeaturesString), activeWindow, *firstFrame, *frame);
2629 if (newFrameOrException.hasException())
2630 return newFrameOrException.releaseException();
2631
2632 auto newFrame = newFrameOrException.releaseReturnValue();
2633 return newFrame ? &newFrame->windowProxy() : RefPtr<WindowProxy> { nullptr };
2634}

2636void DOMWindow::showModalDialog(const String& urlString, const String& dialogFeaturesString, DOMWindow& activeWindow, DOMWindow& firstWindow, const WTF::Function<void (DOMWindow&)>& prepareDialogFunction)
2637{
2638 if (!isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
2639 return;
2640 if (!activeWindow.frame())
2641 return;
2642 Frame* firstFrame = firstWindow.frame();
2643 if (!firstFrame)
2644 return;
2645
2646 auto* frame = this->frame();
2647 auto* page = frame->page();
2648 if (!page)
2649 return;
2650
2651 if (!page->arePromptsAllowed()) {
2652 printErrorMessage("Use of window.showModalDialog is not allowed while unloading a page.");
2653 return;
2654 }
2655
2656 if (!canShowModalDialog(*frame) || !firstWindow.allowPopUp())
2657 return;
2658
2659 auto dialogFrameOrException = createWindow(urlString, emptyAtom(), parseDialogFeatures(dialogFeaturesString, screenAvailableRect(frame->view())), activeWindow, *firstFrame, *frame, prepareDialogFunction);
2660 if (dialogFrameOrException.hasException())
